HEADWORD: Melanuric
<hw>Mel`a*nu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Melam</ets>
+ <ets>urea</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
designating, a complex nitrogenous acid obtained by decomposition of
melam, or of urea, as a white crystalline powder; -- called also
<altname>melanurenic acid</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

